 -- VisorCraft LLC <licensing@visorcraft.com>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 22:33:00 -0500

linsync (1.9.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Remove *all* automatic defaults for the Compare page's Left and Right path
    fields. On a bare launch (the normal case: no two positional arguments on
    the command line), the editors now always start empty, showing the
    placeholders "Left file or folder" / "Right file or folder". Previous
    "last session" (whether from fixtures, /tmp/bigfolder, real user compares,
    or anything) is no longer auto-applied to populate the inputs or the
    initial diff view. The "Restore last session" setting and the recent-
    sessions store / Sessions sidebar remain fully functional for *explicit*
    resume (click to re-open a previous compare or multi-tab workspace); that
    action will then set the paths. This finally eliminates the "why are we
    defaulting to fake folder names" problem.
  * Implementation: on bare launch the open_last_session path still cleans
    internal fixtures out of the recent list (for the Sessions page), but no
    longer synthesizes a launch context that would drive the path properties
    in QML. Only explicit CLI launches, UI browse/type, drag, or explicit
    reopen set non-empty values in the path fields.

 -- VisorCraft LLC <licensing@visorcraft.com>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 18:23:00 -0500

linsync (1.9.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * UX: prevent the Compare page's Left/Right path editors from defaulting to
    internal test fixture paths (e.g. .../tests/fixtures/folders/left) on bare
    GUI launches. Paths under the source tree's tests/fixtures/ (used heavily
    by gui-smoke.sh, release-smoke, unit tests, and dev `cargo run -p linsync -- ...`)
    are now excluded from recent-paths and recent-sessions storage by
    tab_has_persistable_paths(), and filtered out of the in-memory recent list
    on load/restore. The Sessions page (/sessions/recent) and reopen handler
    also drop them. This stops dev/smoke usage from permanently polluting the
    user's XDG_STATE_HOME recent-sessions.json (and thus the auto-restore when
    open_last_session=true). Updated the affected tests to use clean temp files.
  * The root cause was that the fixtures are real, comparable data (so
    validation.compatible was true) and there was no exclusion for repo-internal
    test data in the "persist recent" path.

 -- VisorCraft LLC <licensing@visorcraft.com>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 18:15:00 -0500

linsync (1.9.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CI and test reliability: set LINSYNC_SANDBOX_SKIP=1 in the Justfile `test:`
    recipe (and documented in .github/workflows/ci.yml and the sandbox
    integration test module doc) so that `just ci` and `just test` are reliable
    and non-flaky across containers, GitHub runners, and dev shells; the
    Landlock/seccomp enforcement tests that assert real EACCES are still
    exercised by running the specific test without the variable on a kernel+env
    where enforcement works.
  * Packaging robustness: packaging/appimage/build-appdir.sh now forces Qt 6
    qmake (QMAKE=qmake6 or qmake-qt6) before invoking linuxdeploy --plugin qt,
    avoiding "Could not find Qt modules" when a stray qmake-qt5 is first on
    PATH; the Justfile `package:` recipe now defaults the builder to
    NO_STRIP=1 (the strip binary inside current linuxdeploy AppImages fails on
    some .relr.dyn sections from staged host libraries on modern toolchains);
    `just package` and the makepkg path now succeed and produce functional
    AppDir / .AppImage / .pkg.tar.zst out of the box.
  * Release preflight: docs/parity-acceptance.md now has explicit rows for
    every area listed in docs/feature-parity.md (including the split
    "Specialized compare — image", "— document", "— webpage", "— archive", and
    the standalone "Plugin sandbox"), so `python3 scripts/check-parity-acceptance.py`
    (called from scripts/release-smoke.sh) passes.
  * Minor cleanups from the full build/audit cycle: spurious modified status on
    binary test fixtures after smoke runs is now suppressed via index refresh.

